707342f-a.title: Brooklyn: West End Ave. - Hampton Ave.
707342f-a.text:
12O West End Ave.. (rear view shown) west side, south of Hampton Av.,
showing at the extreme right No. 117 (no street) facing part of the Loig
Island R.P. right of way. To the left are a group of sheds, once a part of
the pumping station for this area.
December 1923.
Eurene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

707341f-a.title: Brooklyn: West End Ave. - Hampton Ave.
707341f-a.text:
West End Ave., east side, between Hampton Ave., and Oriental Boulevard
(street is in the background). The frame house to the left of the right
of way in the background, is No. 120 West End Ave. The Long Island R.R.
right of way is also seen. This area comprises 12 acres, vhich extends north
from Brighton Beach through to Neptune Aves, with frontage on Shore Ave.
Upon this site ~hich is near a fully developed community will be erected
apartments and stores. For further information see the New York Sun,
February 11, 1937.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
